HEADWORD: Psalmody
<hw>Psal"mo*dy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/; <?/ psalm
+ <?/ a song, an ode: cf. F. <ets>psalmodie</ets>, LL.
<ets>psalmodia</ets>. See <er>Psalm</er>, and <er>Ode</er>.]</ety>
<def>The act, practice, or art of singing psalms or sacred songs; also,
